      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the best primer design tool?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The best primer design tool depends on your application. For basic PCR, Primer3 is widely used but only handles primer picking. For validated, lab-ready designs, VigyanLLM's 22-step pipeline adds BLAST specificity checking, SNP filtering, secondary structure analysis, thermodynamic validation, multiplex compatibility scoring, and audit-ready reporting — all automated in a single run. This comprehensive validation eliminates the manual cross-checking that Primer3 users typically need to perform separately."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does VigyanLLM validate primer designs?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "VigyanLLM's 22-step pipeline validates primer designs through: (1) transcript isoform selection, (2) exon-intron mapping, (3) bisulfite compatibility check, (4) degenerate base handling, (5) repeat masking, (6) Primer3 design, (7) nearest-neighbor Tm calculation, (8) buffer composition correction, (9) Mg2+ correction, (10) BLAST specificity, (11) Bowtie2 alignment, (12) organelle genome screening, (13) secondary structure analysis, (14) amplicon structure check, (15) dbSNP filtering, (16) ClinVar annotation, (17) adapter tailing, (18) multiplex scoring, (19) penalty ranking, (20) thermocycling profile, (21) manufacturing QC, and (22) probe design. Each step produces a documented, auditable result."
      }
    },
